Went in for lunch on a Sunday and this place was PACKED and for very good reason! Absolutely loved el desayuno mixto (plantains, beans, crema, and a papusa of choice) and papusas frijoles (beans), camarones (shrimp), and calabaza (squash). They also carry half liter Mexican Coca Cola (made with real sugar and imported) in glass bottles. The sides (rice, beans, crema, and slaw) were all fantastic. If you've never had Salvadorian food, I highly encourage you to give this place a shot! Great service and DELICIOUS food.

Authentic and cheap Ecuadorean food, right down to the spicy curtido (cole slaw) and unrefrigerated mayo. Not exactly your healthiest option, but there's something for most everyone here. Wide variety of pupusas are the star - I would recommend the jalapeno if you like it spicy, also check out the loroco (a green similar to spinach). You can get them with or without cheese. I've also had the fried plantains, yuca frita, and some empanadas. Everything is simple and delicious. They also have classic Latin American drinks like horchata and agua de jamaica.  Don't go expecting fine dining or much in the way of salads, but if you feel like some down-home Central American cuisine, this is a great place. The parking lot and premises aren't much to look at, but the kitchen is where it counts!
